  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-fried-rice-with-halloumi-and-chilli-mayo/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and dice</p><p>Peel and chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice your<strong> halloumi</strong> into 3 pieces per person</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-fried-rice-with-halloumi-and-chilli-mayo/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the<strong> diced pepper </strong>to the pan with a little <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-fried-rice-with-halloumi-and-chilli-mayo/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>mayo</strong> and <strong>sriracha </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) <strong> </strong>in a small bowl with a generous pinch of your <strong>peri peri spice mix</strong></p><p>Add a splash of cold water and give everything a good mix up – this is your <strong>chilli mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-fried-rice-with-halloumi-and-chilli-mayo/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Squeeze your pouch[es] of <strong>cooked white long grain rice </strong>to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>(just a little!) and <strong>microwave </strong>for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two or more pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-fried-rice-with-halloumi-and-chilli-mayo/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pepper is soft, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and the <strong>remaining peri peri spice mix</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 30 secs until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>cooked white long grain rice</strong> and <strong>blanched peas</strong> to the pan along with a splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Stir it all together and cook for 1-2 min or until warmed through – this is your <strong>peri peri fried rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-fried-rice-with-halloumi-and-chilli-mayo/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a separate pan over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halloumi pieces </strong>and<strong> </strong>cook on each side for 1-2 min until golden</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/peri-peri-fried-rice-with-halloumi-and-chilli-mayo/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>peri peri fried rice </strong>and top with the <strong>pan-fried halloumi</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>chilli mayo </strong>over everything</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
